          <msContents>
            <summary> Ff. 5r–169v: Psalter, Dawit, ዳዊት; Ff. 5r–134r: Psalms of David, መዝሙር ዘዳዊት, the Psalms begin with a strophe from the Psalter of the Virgin [f. 5r], the word for God is not rubricated in the psalms, the midpoint of the Psalms is unmarked in Psalm 77 [f. 70r], Psalm 119 has only the Hebrew letters at the head of each section, without an interpretation, Psalm 151 contains the short version; Ff. 134r–148r: Biblical Canticles, መሓልየ ነቢያት; Ff. 148r–155r: Song of Songs, መኃልየ መኃልይ, common version. Ff. 155v–167v: Praises of Mary, ውዳሴ ማርያም, arranged for the days of the week: Monday (f. 155v), Tuesday (f. 156v), Wednesday (f. 158r), Thursday (f. 160r), Friday (f. 162v), Saturday (f. 164r), Sunday (f. 165r); Ff. 167v–170v: Gate of Light, አንቀጸ ብርሃን, incomplete at the very end.
            </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
              <locus from="5r" to="169v" facs="005">Fols 5r–169v</locus>
              <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
              <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                <locus from="5r" to="134r" facs="005">Fols 5r–134r</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                <note>Psalm 118 has only the Hebrew letters at the head of each section, without an
                  interpretation. Psalm 151 contains the short version</note>
                <note><locus target="#5r" facs="005">Fol. 5r</locus><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</ref>
                  begin with a strophe from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3985Mazmura">Mazmura
                                                  Dǝngǝl</ref></note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                <locus from="134r" to="148r" facs="134">Fols 134r–148r</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
                <note><locus target="#139r" facs="139">Fol. 139r</locus><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2257salota#Hannah"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2257salota#Hannah</span></ref>, here identified as <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎተ፡ ሐና፡ አመ፡ ሰሙኤል፡</foreign>, Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel</q></note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                <locus from="148r" to="155r" facs="148">Fols 148r–155r</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">common version</title>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                <locus from="155v" to="167v" facs="156">Fols 155v–167v</locus>
                <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse
                                                  Māryām</title>
                <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4.1">
                  <locus from="155v" facs="156">Fols 155v and following</locus>
